    "what_description": "Chamomilla recutita is an annual plant belonging to the family Asteraceae. It has a taproot and a single stem that grows up to 20-50 cm in height, with a diameter of 1-3 mm. The stem is hairy and branched, with ovate to lanceolate leaves that are 1-5 cm long and 0.5-2 cm wide, having a serrated margin and a hairy underside. The plant produces small white or pale yellow flowers in a capitulum, which is an inflorescence of numerous small flowers. The flowers are 8-12 mm in diameter, with a daisy-like appearance and a prominent tubular corolla.",
