    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Chamomilla recutita are attributed to its ability to reduce inflammation, which contributes to its effectiveness in treating conditions like eczema and dermatitis. The bioactive compounds responsible for this anti-inflammatory effect include apigenin, a flavonoid, and bisabolol, a sesquiterpene alcohol. Furthermore, the antioxidant properties of Chamomilla recutita, which are largely due to the presence of luteolin and apigenin, help protect the plant's constituents from oxidative damage and enhance their bioavailability. The sedative properties of this plant, which are mediated by the volatile oils alpha-bisabolol and alpha-bisabolene, can aid in promoting relaxation and reducing anxiety. Additionally, the antimicrobial and analgesic properties of Chamomilla recutita, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and sesquiterpene hydrocarbons, enable it to inhibit the growth of bacteria and fungi, and alleviate pain associated with headaches and other conditions.",
