    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Chamomilla recutita are apigenin, luteolin, alpha-bisabolol, chrysin, and \u03b1-bisabolol. Apigenin and luteolin are flavonoids that exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties by scavenging free radicals and inhibiting pro-inflammatory enzymes, such as COX-2 and LOX. Alpha-bisabolol and \u03b1-bisabolol are sesquiterpene alcohols that exhibit anti-inflammatory, antiseptic, and soothing properties by reducing inflammation and modulating the immune response. Chrysin, a flavonoid, has been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties by inhibiting COX-2 and inducing apoptosis in inflammatory cells. These constituents work together to provide a broad spectrum of healing effects, including anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and soothing properties, making Chamomilla recutita a valuable herb in traditional medicine.",
