    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Chamomilla recutita are tincture, tea, salve, infusion, and essential oil. The tincture is a concentrated liquid extract of the plant's flowers, typically used for its anti-inflammatory and antispasmodic properties. Tea made from the flowers of Chamomilla recutita is used to soothe digestive issues and promote relaxation, with a recommended dosage of 1-2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water. A salve is a topical preparation used to treat skin irritations, wounds, and minor burns, typically containing a mixture of the plant's essential oil and a carrier oil. The essential oil of Chamomilla recutita, obtained through steam distillation, is used in aromatherapy to calm nervous anxiety and promote a restful sleep, with a recommended dosage of 5-10 drops per diffuser.",
