    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Chamomilla recutita improperly include exacerbating allergies due to its potential allergenic compounds, such as sesquiterpene lactones and apigenin, which can trigger allergic reactions. This is because some individuals may be sensitive to these compounds, leading to an allergic response. Additionally, ingesting large amounts of Chamomilla recutita may trigger asthma attacks in people with pre-existing respiratory conditions. Furthermore, consuming excessive amounts can cause dizziness due to its sedative properties, which may interact with other medications or exacerbate underlying health conditions. It is also possible to induce allergic reactions with topical application of Chamomilla recutita, especially in individuals with skin sensitivities."
